## Plan-artifact canonical contract

Full schema, per-section shapes, per-list caps, and string-length tiers live in `.agent/artifact-formats/plan.md`. Topics previously inlined as pointer H2 sections (Intent & intent_verb, Step contract, Plan size limits, Cycle guard, Module family, StepType reference, Step ↔ acceptance-criteria linking, Design section, Plan-artifact payload) are all defined there. The closed-set reference for `step_type` is preserved inline below as `Common StepType mistakes`.

## Common StepType mistakes

- Do NOT use `step_type: "test"` — there is no test step_type. Use `step_type: "verify"` with `verify_command: "pytest tests/test_x.py -q"` for test-running steps.
- Do NOT use `step_type: "check"`, `step_type: "run"`, or any other ad-hoc label. The closed set is `file_change`, `action`, `research`, `verify`.
- If a step does not modify a file and does not run a verification command, it is `action` (a non-mutating executor action) or `research` (an exploratory step with no committed change).

Use only canonical step types: `file_change`, `action`, `research`, or `verify`. For test-running steps, set `step_type` to `verify` and include `verify_command` or `location`.

